article.headline: Montana St. 82, Oregon St. 79
article.story: CORVALLIS, Ore. -- Will Bynum had 23 points and six steals to lead Montana State to an 82-79 overtime win against Oregon State on Wednesday. Bobby Howard added 20 points for Montana State (2-2). The Bobcats won for the second time in Corvallis in as many seasons. Oregon State (0-4) couldn't hold a 15-point second-half lead and in turn lost its 25th straight game dating back to December of last season. Omari Johnson missed a 3-pointer at the buzzer that would have tied the score. Rickey Claitt had a career-high 21 points for the Beavers.
